OF COURSE. WELL,
I DON'T KNOW, ACTUALLY.
(glggleS)

29:26.490 --> 29:27.923
I NEVER REALLY ASKED.
OLIVER.

29:27.960 --> 29:29.052
HI.
HEY, I WAS HOPING
I'D SEE YOU.

29:29.100 --> 29:30.226
I-I WASN'T SURE YOU WERE
GONNA MAKE IT.

29:30.260 --> 29:32.569
YEAH. WELL, UM...
I'M HERE.

29:32.600 --> 29:33.897
HI.
MM-HMM.

29:33.940 --> 29:35.464
UH, SORRY. UM...
ZOE, THIS IS CELERY.

29:35.500 --> 29:36.933
CELERY, THIS IS ZOE.
HI.

29:36.970 --> 29:38.130
I-I'M SORRY.
WHAT'S YOUR NAME?

29:38.170 --> 29:39.467
CELERY.
LIKE THE VEGETABLE.

29:39.510 --> 29:41.535
THE ONE YOUR KIDS
PROBABLY DON'T EAT.

29:41.580 --> 29:43.036
WHAT DO YOU KNOW
ABOUT MY KIDS?

29:43.080 --> 29:44.877
OH, HOLD ON. UM...
(stammers)

29:44.910 --> 29:46.571
EXCUSE US.
JUST GIVE US A SECOND.

29:46.610 --> 29:49.443
ZOE... COME ON!
WHAT?

29:49.480 --> 29:52.916
WELL, YOU'RE HERE WITH MAX,
AND I AM HERE WITH CELERY,

29:52.950 --> 29:55.453
SO WE'RE GONNA BE COOL.
MAX DIDN'T COME.

29:55.490 --> 29:58.186
WE BROKE UP
A COUPLE DAYS AGO.

29:58.230 --> 29:59.822
I'M SORRY TO HEAR THAT.
NO, YOU'RE NOT.

29:59.860 --> 30:01.953
ACTUALLY, I AM.

30:02.000 --> 30:03.922
I AM. COME HERE.

30:03.970 --> 30:05.221
(kisses)

30:05.270 --> 30:07.898
WE'LL TALK LATER.
OKAY?
OKAY.

30:07.940 --> 30:09.589
OKAY. ALL RIGHT.

30:09.640 --> 30:11.130
THAT'S... I'M SORRY.

30:11.170 --> 30:14.105
(indistinct conversations)

30:21.550 --> 30:23.541
MAY I TAKE YOUR COAT?
I THOUGHT WE WERE MEETING
AT THE BAR.

30:23.580 --> 30:25.184
COAT CHECK GIRL
HASN'T SHOWN UP.

30:25.220 --> 30:26.585
FIGURED I'D WAIT
FOR YOU HERE.

30:26.620 --> 30:28.952
HANG A FEW COATS.
OH, HOW VERY WEIRD OF YOU.

30:28.990 --> 30:32.050
I'VE MADE 20 BUCKS.

30:32.090 --> 30:33.921
MAKE THAT $22.

30:33.960 --> 30:35.257
IN THE JAR, PLEASE.

30:35.300 --> 30:37.154
(rattles)

30:38.500 --> 30:39.569
TIP?

30:39.600 --> 30:41.431
I ONLY HAVE A $5.

30:42.570 --> 30:45.061
WOW!

30:45.110 --> 30:46.463
YOU KNOW WHAT?
I HATE THESE THINGS.

30:46.510 --> 30:47.977
EVERYONE'S MILLING AROUND.

30:48.010 --> 30:49.375
I MEAN, THEY'RE LAUGHING
AND THEY'RE CARING.

30:49.410 --> 30:52.072
I KNOW. IT'S AWFUL.
I USUALLY DODGE THIS STUFF,

30:52.110 --> 30:54.544
BUT YOU NEEDED A LAST-MINUTE
PLUS-ONE

30:54.580 --> 30:57.344
AND I AM ALL ABOUT
GROWING THESE DAYS.

30:57.380 --> 30:59.416
SO...

30:59.450 --> 31:01.509
(sets glasses down)
MACARENA?

31:04.460 --> 31:06.325
LET'S JUST GET THIS OVER WITH.

31:06.360 --> 31:08.021
THANK YOU SO MUCH
FOR HELPING ME.

31:08.060 --> 31:09.596
NO PROBLEM.
UH, WHO IS TAFFY?

31:09.630 --> 31:11.621
TAFFY? TAF--

31:11.670 --> 31:14.468
TRACI. IT'S MY FIRST TIME
USING A CALLIGRAPHY PEN.

31:14.500 --> 31:17.333
WHERE?
SHE'S HERE.

31:17.370 --> 31:19.201
WHERE'S NOELLE?
UH... I-I HAVEN'T SEEN HER.

31:19.240 --> 31:21.208
SHE--SHE'S NOT HERE YET?
NO. WHY?

31:21.240 --> 31:23.538
SHE DISAPPEARED.
NOBODY KNOWS WHERE SHE IS.
WHAT? WHAT?

31:23.580 --> 31:26.344
D-DON'T TELL FRANK.
HE DOESN'T KNOW. SHH.

31:26.380 --> 31:28.541
(claps hands)
HEY. OKAY.

31:28.580 --> 31:30.980
SO, WHERE'S MY BEAUTIFUL
FIANCE?

31:34.520 --> 31:38.081
SHE'S... NOT FEELING WELL.
I THINK SHE'S ON HER WAY
DOWN, I THINK. WHAT?

31:38.130 --> 31:40.052
ALL RIGHT,
WHAT'S GOING ON, GUYS?

31:42.260 --> 31:44.262
ALL RIGHT, EPSTEIN, WHAT
THE HELL'S GOING ON AROUND HERE?

31:45.470 --> 31:46.619
I'M DATING CHLOE.

31:46.670 --> 31:49.264
YOU'RE WHAT?
YEAH. I-I'M DATING CHLOE.

31:49.300 --> 31:51.404
YOUR GODDAUGHTER,
YOUR BRIDESMAID,

31:51.440 --> 31:52.998
AND, YES, MY COLLEAGUE.

31:53.040 --> 31:54.701
BUT THE THING IS,
IT STARTED BEFORE SHE DID.

31:54.740 --> 31:56.605
I MEAN, B-B-BEFORE
SHE STARTED AT 15,

31:56.640 --> 31:58.176
NOT BEFORE SHE STARTED
TO EXIST--

31:58.210 --> 32:00.041
FRANK. FRANK.
STAFF--

32:00.080 --> 32:03.208
SIR. UH, NOELLE'S HERE.

32:03.250 --> 32:05.389
SHE NEEDS TO TALK TO YOU.

32:09.260 --> 32:11.080
(sighs)

32:11.130 --> 32:12.324
YEAH.

32:12.360 --> 32:14.954
SO, WHAT? WE DON'T GET
TO TALK ABOUT THIS?

32:15.000 --> 32:16.353
FRANK, PLEASE.

32:16.400 --> 32:18.220
I HAVE BEEN WHERE YOU ARE
WITH MY OWN FAMILY.

32:18.270 --> 32:20.966
THERE IS NO WAY
TO PREPARE FOR THIS.

32:21.000 --> 32:22.262
IT'S JUST BETTER THIS WAY,
ALL RIGHT?

32:22.300 --> 32:24.962
AT LEAST, LIKE, UNTIL
I CAN FIGURE OUT--
WH--BETTER FOR WHO?

32:25.010 --> 32:27.331
ME? OLIVIA? YOU?

32:27.370 --> 32:32.103
LOOK, WHATEVER HAPPENS,
WE WILL GET THROUGH IT.

32:32.150 --> 32:33.401
YOU AND ME.

32:33.450 --> 32:35.475
SAME AS IT--IT
ALWAYS HAS BEEN.

32:35.520 --> 32:37.613
WHAT IF I DON'T WANT
TO GET THROUGH IT TOGETHER?

32:37.650 --> 32:40.118
WHAT IF I CAN'T?

32:40.150 --> 32:41.754
THEN I GUESS YOU'RE GONNA
HAVE TO TRY HARDER

32:41.790 --> 32:43.758
TO SHAKE ME LOOSE.

32:43.790 --> 32:45.189
I'M NOT LETTING YOU
WALK AWAY FROM US

32:45.230 --> 32:47.084
BECAUSE OF SOMETHING
THAT MAY

32:47.130 --> 32:48.688
OR MAY NOT HAPPEN, BABY.

32:48.730 --> 32:51.324
SOMETHING THAT I WOULD
WANT TO BE HERE FOR.

32:51.370 --> 32:53.565
(exhales)
LISTEN TO ME. SWEETHEART.

32:55.700 --> 32:57.292
BABY, IT'S JUST ME.

32:59.440 --> 33:01.635
IT'S JUST ME.

33:01.680 --> 33:03.534
ALL RIGHT.

33:10.220 --> 33:12.518
(exhales)
IT'S GONNA BE ALL RIGHT.

33:13.790 --> 33:15.348
I'M SORRY.

33:15.390 --> 33:16.618
IT'S NOT YOUR FAULT.

33:16.660 --> 33:18.753
I KNOW. IT'S JUST...

33:18.790 --> 33:20.451
I KNOW YOU REALLY
WANTED TO BE THERE.

33:20.490 --> 33:22.355
IT'S FINE.
NAH.

33:22.400 --> 33:23.628
NOT REALLY.
(beeps)

33:23.660 --> 33:27.221
(phone rings)

33:27.270 --> 33:28.589
(beeps)
(laughing)

33:28.640 --> 33:30.494
Hey, Dov?
(lowered voice)
WHERE ARE YOU GUYS?

33:30.540 --> 33:32.508
WE'RE WORKING. YOU?

33:32.540 --> 33:33.768
UH, JUST WAITING
FOR THE BRIDE TO SHOW UP,

33:33.810 --> 33:35.573
BUT I GOTTA GO.
IT'S GONNA START SOON.

33:35.610 --> 33:38.499
UH, HEY, HEY, UH...
YOU GOT SPEAKERPHONE?

33:38.550 --> 33:40.404
ARE YOU SERIOUS?
COME ON.

33:40.450 --> 33:42.077
WE'LL PUT OUR END ON MUTE.
WE JUST WANT TO LISTEN.

33:42.120 --> 33:43.371
YEAH, SURE.
I GUESS IT CAN'T GET ANY WORSE.

33:43.420 --> 33:44.785
(chuckles)
(phone beeps)

33:44.820 --> 33:46.685
(laughing) SORRY.

33:46.720 --> 33:48.312
(Wagner's "Bridal Chorus"
from "Lohengrin" playing)

33:48.360 --> 33:50.316
THERE IT IS.
THAT'S THE RIFF.

33:50.360 --> 33:51.452
SHE'S COMING IN.

33:51.490 --> 33:54.425
**

33:57.400 --> 33:59.789
(Noelle chuckles)

34:06.440 --> 34:09.500
(music continues
over speakerphone)

34:09.540 --> 34:12.304
**

34:14.550 --> 34:16.142
(music ends)

34:16.180 --> 34:17.579
DEARLY BELOVED,

34:17.620 --> 34:20.418
WE ARE GATHERED HERE
TOGETHER TODAY TO JOIN FRANK

34:20.450 --> 34:22.589
and Noelle
in holy matrimony.

34:22.620 --> 34:24.121
I ACTUALLY WISH
WE WERE THERE.

34:24.160 --> 34:25.650
ME, TOO.

34:25.690 --> 34:27.658
THERE'S NOWHERE I'D RATHER
BE THAN HERE, THOUGH.

34:27.690 --> 34:30.250
JUST...

34:30.300 --> 34:33.292
YOU AND ME SITTING HERE,
DOING WHAT WE DO.

34:34.840 --> 34:38.105
I, Franklin Joseph Best,

34:38.140 --> 34:41.530
TAKE YOU,
NOELLE GRACE WILLIAMS,

34:41.580 --> 34:44.140
TO BE MY LAWFUL WEDDED WIFE,

34:44.180 --> 34:45.841
TO HAVE AND TO HOLD,

34:45.880 --> 34:49.372
FROM THIS DAY FORWARD,

34:49.420 --> 34:51.183
FOR BETTER OR WORSE,

34:51.220 --> 34:54.280
IN SICKNESS AND IN HEALTH,

34:54.320 --> 34:57.517
TO LOVE AND CHERISH,

34:57.560 --> 34:59.778
till death do us part.

34:59.830 --> 35:01.798
(sniffles and laughs)

35:01.830 --> 35:03.149
(minister) Noelle?
OH...

35:03.200 --> 35:05.259
IT GETS ME EVERY TIME.

35:05.300 --> 35:06.790
I DON'T KNOW WHY.

35:06.830 --> 35:08.798
YOU KNOW? I KNOW THE WORDS
LIKE THE BACK OF MY HAND,

35:08.840 --> 35:10.796
BUT SOMEHOW...

35:10.840 --> 35:12.660
I DON'T KNOW, THEY JUST
GET MORE MAGICAL,

35:12.710 --> 35:14.678
YOU KNOW, EVERY TIME
I HEAR THEM.

35:14.710 --> 35:17.133
THAT'S HOW I FEEL
ABOUT YOU.

35:17.180 --> 35:19.501
WHAT, THAT MY WORDS GET
MORE MAGICAL? (chuckles)

35:19.550 --> 35:20.676
NO.

35:20.710 --> 35:21.847
YOU DO.

35:21.880 --> 35:23.711
(Noelle)
...to love and cherish...

35:23.750 --> 35:25.240
IT'S CRAZY, RIGHT?

35:25.290 --> 35:26.814
till death do us part.

35:26.850 --> 35:28.215
NO, I JUST--

35:30.420 --> 35:32.149
YEAH, SORRY TO INTERRUPT.

35:32.190 --> 35:35.159
I WANTED TO LET YOU KNOW
JAMIE'S ON HIS WAY DOWN.
THANK YOU.

35:35.200 --> 35:37.395
(radio chatter)

35:37.430 --> 35:39.762
JAMESON WARD?
I'M OFFICER MCNALLY.

35:39.800 --> 35:41.438
THIS IS OFFICER COLLINS.

35:41.470 --> 35:43.290
CAN YOU TELL US WHERE YOU
WERE THIS MORNING,

35:43.340 --> 35:45.308
APPROXIMATELY 10:30 A.M.?
WHAT'S THIS ABOUT?
WHAT'S GOING ON?

35:45.340 --> 35:46.830
WELL, THERE WAS A BUS ROBBERY
AT THAT TIME.

35:46.870 --> 35:47.905
WE GOT REASON TO BELIEVE--
NO. JUST--

35:47.940 --> 35:49.908
WE JUST WANT TO TALK
TO YOU FOR A FEW MORE MINUTES.

35:49.940 --> 35:52.374
COME ON, COME BACK DOWN HERE!

35:52.410 --> 35:54.878
(sighs) JAMESON WARD,
YOU ARE UNDER ARREST

35:54.920 --> 35:58.219
FOR... EVADING ARREST.

35:58.250 --> 35:59.842
THAT'S A GOOD ONE.
I DON'T KNOW.

35:59.890 --> 36:01.915
(stammers)
SO WHAT DO YOU THINK?

36:01.960 --> 36:04.383
I MEAN, WHERE'S HE
GONNA GO, RIGHT?

36:04.430 --> 36:06.523
DO YOU WANNA GO AFTER HIM?
'CAUSE I'M GAME IF YOU WANT TO.

36:06.560 --> 36:08.357
NO. WHAT'S THE POINT?

36:08.400 --> 36:09.958
THERE'S NO RUSH.

36:10.000 --> 36:11.058
(reverse signal beeping,
radio static)

36:11.100 --> 36:14.365
1504, WE GOT EYES ON
THE SUSPECT IN THE BUS ROBBERY.

36:14.400 --> 36:16.391
HE'S, UH...

36:16.440 --> 36:17.930
HE'S CLIMBED 70 FEET
UP THE TOWER.

36:17.970 --> 36:19.506
WE COULD USE A LITTLE
BACKUP.
(radio static)

36:19.540 --> 36:22.179
(woman) Copy, 1504.
(radio static)

36:29.750 --> 36:31.411
SO WHAT DO WE DO NOW?

36:31.450 --> 36:33.509
I DON'T KNOW.

36:33.550 --> 36:35.211
(scoffs)

36:35.260 --> 36:37.319
IT'S CRAZY, RIGHT?

36:38.990 --> 36:41.185
THAT'S WHAT YOU SAID.

36:42.300 --> 36:44.268
I GUESS THAT'S UP TO YOU.

36:46.630 --> 36:49.428
(breathes sharply)

37:10.060 --> 37:12.483
(laughter)
AH! IT'S THE FIRST DANCE!

37:12.530 --> 37:14.498
(Jill Barber)
* LONG AS THIS WORLD
GO AHEAD.

37:14.530 --> 37:16.589
(cheering)
(man) FRANKIE AND NOELLE!

37:16.630 --> 37:18.268
* KEEPS SPINNIN' AROUND

37:18.300 --> 37:19.597
MR. AND MRS.!

37:19.630 --> 37:22.463
* I'LL KEEP HOLDING ON

37:22.500 --> 37:26.709
* TO THIS LOVE
THAT I FOUND *

37:26.740 --> 37:29.538
* I WON'T LET GO

37:29.580 --> 37:31.707
(laughter)
OH-HO-HO! OH!

37:31.750 --> 37:33.377
I'M GONNA GET ANOTHER DRINK.
DO YOU WANT ONE?

37:33.410 --> 37:34.946
YEAH, PLEASE.

37:34.980 --> 37:38.279
* AND I WILL NEVER,
EVER QUIT LOVING YOU *

37:38.320 --> 37:39.617
IT'S NOT TOO LATE.

37:39.650 --> 37:41.311
WE HAVEN'T CONSUMMATED
THE UNION.

37:41.360 --> 37:43.282
YOU COULD RUN OUT THE DOOR,
ANNUL THE MARRIAGE.

37:43.320 --> 37:45.356
THEN LET'S DO IT RIGHT NOW.

37:45.390 --> 37:46.584
WHAT?

37:47.730 --> 37:49.493
CONSUMMATE THE UNION.

37:49.530 --> 37:50.724
(both laugh)

37:50.760 --> 37:52.921
MAYBE WE SHOULD FINISH
THE SONG.

37:52.970 --> 37:55.689
I THINK WE'D HAVE
A GOOD TIME, THOUGH.
(laughing)
I THINK SO, TOO.

37:55.740 --> 37:57.367
COME JOIN US.
PLEASE.

37:57.400 --> 37:58.833
GET OUT THERE.

37:58.870 --> 38:00.565
WANNA GO OUT THERE?
I DON'T REALLY
CARE TO DANCE.

38:00.610 --> 38:02.077
AH, COME ON, YOU NEED IT.

38:02.110 --> 38:03.771
* FEELING BLUE

38:03.810 --> 38:06.540
* THATﬂI EVE-R- NEVER

38:06.580 --> 38:09.447
* EVER QUIT LOVING YOU

38:09.480 --> 38:11.812
(both laugh)

38:13.490 --> 38:16.880
HEY, UH... THEY LOOK
GREAT, HUH?

38:16.920 --> 38:19.889
**

38:21.460 --> 38:22.825
HERE YOU GO.
THANKS.

38:22.860 --> 38:24.418
I DON'T WANT TO INTERRUPT.
I'M JUST GONNA--

38:24.470 --> 38:25.823
I'M GONNA HEAD OUT.
WHAT?

38:25.870 --> 38:28.088
UM... WAIT.
WHERE ARE YOU GOING?

38:28.130 --> 38:29.995
MM...

38:30.040 --> 38:32.964
I JUST THINK YOU HAVE
SOME THINGS TO FIGURE OUT,

38:35.510 --> 38:37.000
I'M JUST GONNA GRAB A CAB.
I'M JUST--

38:37.040 --> 38:38.371
NO HARD FEELINGS.
NO, NO, NO--

38:38.410 --> 38:40.378
NO HARD FEELINGS,
BUT I DON'T.

38:40.410 --> 38:41.718
I HAVE NOTHING TO FIGURE OUT.

38:41.750 --> 38:43.843
THE--THE ONLY THING
THAT I HAVE TO FIGURE OUT

38:43.880 --> 38:46.110
IS HOW I GET THE MOST
BEAUTIFUL WOMAN IN THIS ROOM

38:46.150 --> 38:47.947
TO DANCE WITH ME.
(chuckles)

38:47.990 --> 38:49.810
YOU KNOW, I--
IT'S BEEN A WHILE.

38:49.860 --> 38:51.589
A GOOD, LONG WHILE,
BUT I DANCE ALL THE TIME

38:51.630 --> 38:53.552
WITH MY GIRLS, AND I DON'T
KNOW IF YOU KNOW THIS,

38:53.590 --> 38:56.491
BUT ONE DIRECT ION--THEY JUST
DROPPED A NEW RECORD,

38:56.530 --> 38:58.828
AND I KNOW IT
BACK TO FRONT.
(laughs)

38:58.870 --> 39:01.361
YES.
YES!

39:01.400 --> 39:02.560
WE'RE GONNA DANCE!
(laughs)

39:02.600 --> 39:06.900
**

39:06.940 --> 39:08.601
MMM!

39:08.640 --> 39:10.870
(mouth full) OH, MY GOD!
YOU GOTTA TRY THIS.

39:10.910 --> 39:13.902
WHAT IS IT?
SOME KIND OF CAKE LOLLIPOP.
IT'S AMAZING.

39:13.950 --> 39:15.918
(smacks lips)
TRY IT.

39:17.150 --> 39:18.481
SO? HUH?

39:18.520 --> 39:19.919
(mouth full) KEEP 'EM COMING.
THAT'S GOOD.

39:19.950 --> 39:21.815
KEEP 'EM COMING!
OH, YES. (laughing)
THAT'S GOOD.

39:21.860 --> 39:23.885
MM-HMM. (laughing)
THERE YOU GO.

39:23.920 --> 39:26.457
YOU KNOW THE BEST PART
ABOUT TONIGHT?
YOUR OUTFIT.

39:26.490 --> 39:28.993
MAID OF HONOR IN RUNNING SHOES.
I KNOW. CLASSIC.

39:31.770 --> 39:33.169
YOU DID GOOD.

39:33.200 --> 39:34.929
SO DID YOU.

39:36.600 --> 39:38.602
UM, SO WHAT WAS
THE BEST PART ABOUT TONIGHT?

39:38.640 --> 39:39.959
HMM?
THE HEART-SHAPED BROWNIES.

39:40.010 --> 39:41.807
WHERE?
COVERED IN GOLD LEAF.

39:41.840 --> 39:43.478
THEY'VE BEEN COMING BY
EVERY FIVE MINUTES.

39:43.510 --> 39:44.772
THERE SHE IS.

39:44.810 --> 39:46.846
MMM.
(laughs)

39:48.010 --> 39:49.716
DON'T MOVE. STAY HERE.

39:49.750 --> 39:51.684
I'LL BE RIGHT BACK.
OKAY.

39:51.720 --> 39:54.518
("Dancing With Your Ghost"
Playing)

39:54.560 --> 39:56.187
(Holly laughing)

39:56.220 --> 39:58.529
UM...

39:58.560 --> 40:01.950
SO IS IT STILL FUN
GETTING DRESSED?

40:02.000 --> 40:03.524
(laughs)
WHAT DO YOU MEAN?

40:03.560 --> 40:05.528
WELL, I MEAN, THAT'S
THE MOST FUN PART OF A DATE,

40:05.570 --> 40:07.026
IS GETTING DRESSED.
I MEAN, HOW DOES IT WORK

40:07.070 --> 40:08.628
IF TWO GIRLS ARE GETTING
DRESSED TOGETHER?

40:08.670 --> 40:10.865
I DON'T KNOW.
HOW DOES IT WORK WITH A GUY?

40:10.900 --> 40:12.902
I MEAN, IF YOU LIVE TOGETHER,
HE GETS DRESSED FIRST,

40:12.940 --> 40:15.534
AND THEN YOU GET...
DRESSED.

40:15.580 --> 40:16.831
IT'S VERY STUPID.
STUPID QUESTION.

40:16.880 --> 40:18.609
(Chuckles)

40:18.650 --> 40:20.049
WHAT ABOUT...

40:20.080 --> 40:22.139
IF YOU WANT TO BORROW
A DRESS

40:22.180 --> 40:24.489
OR SHOES OR CLOTHES?

40:24.520 --> 40:27.148
I MEAN, IS THAT COOL? DO YOU
SHARE EACH OTHER'S THINGS?

40:27.190 --> 40:28.851
I WOULDN'T SHARE
YOUR THINGS.

40:28.890 --> 40:30.084
WHAT IS WRONG WITH MY THINGS?

40:30.120 --> 40:32.122
NOTHING. THEY'RE JUST
NOT MY STYLE.

40:32.160 --> 40:35.425
OH, NOT ENOUGH FLEECE FOR YOU,
HOLLY? NOT ENOUGH BACKPACKS?

40:39.670 --> 40:40.989
YOU ARE INSANE.

40:41.030 --> 40:42.861
YOU KNOW THAT, RIGHT?

40:42.900 --> 40:44.936
I'M GONNA TAKE THIS WITH ME,
IF YOU DON'T MIND.

40:44.970 --> 40:46.631
PLENTY MORE OUT THERE.

40:47.910 --> 40:50.105
SORRY. WH--
WHERE ARE YOU GOING?

40:50.140 --> 40:51.744
DANCING.

40:51.780 --> 40:53.099
I KINDA NEED
TO GET IT OUT OF MY SYSTEM.

40:53.150 --> 40:55.618
THANKS. THAT WAS FUN.

40:55.650 --> 40:56.969
PLUS-ONE FOREVER.

40:57.020 --> 40:58.169
* ALL OF THE FACES

40:58.220 --> 41:01.849
* OF THE OTHER PEOPLE
STARING BACK AT ME *

41:01.890 --> 41:04.688
THANK YOU, PAL.
HELP YOURSELF.
NICE SUIT.

41:04.730 --> 41:06.550
OH...
ONE MORE, PLEASE.

41:06.590 --> 41:07.625
THAN KS, MAN.

41:07.660 --> 41:09.890
(laughs)

41:09.930 --> 41:11.898
THIS IS THE FIRST DATE
